title: R-Tools R-Studio Network v7.7.159222 Multilingual
description:
R-Tools R-Studio Network v7.7.159222

R-Studio is a family of powerful and cost-effective un-delete and
data recovery software. Empowered by the new unique data recovery
technologies, it is the most comprehensive data recovery solution
for recovery files from NTFS, NTFS5, ReFS, FAT12/16/32, exFAT,
HFS/HFS+ (Macintosh), Little and Big Endian variants of UFS1/UFS2
(FreeBSD/OpenBSD/NetBSD/Solaris) and Ext2/Ext3/Ext4 FS (Linux)
partitions. It also uses raw file recovery (scan for known file
types) for heavily damaged or unknown file systems. It functions on
local and network disks, even if such partitions are formatted,
damaged or deleted. Flexible parameter settings give you absolute
control over data recovery.

In addition to being a full-featured data recovery utility, R-Studio
also includes:

An advanced RAID reconstruction module
A feature-rich text/hexadecimal editor
An entire advanced disk copying/imaging module in one single piece
of software, which makes R-Studio your ideal complete solution for
creating a data recovery workstation.


Languages:
English, German, French, Spanish, Portuguese, Russian, Japanese,
Chinese.


System Requirements

An Intel-compatible platform running Windows 2000/XP/ 2003/Vista/2008/ Windows 7/8/8.1 / Windows Server 2012.
At least 256 MB of RAM, a mouse, and enough disk space for recovered files, image files, etc.
The administrative privileges are required to install and run R-Studio utilities under Win2000/XP/ 2003/Vista/2008/ Windows 7/8/8.1 / Windows Server 2012.
A network connection for data recovering over network.



Installation:





Unpack, install the application.

Extract patch.rar to the installation directory, overwriting
existing files.

Choose any name/company and use our Keygen to register the
application.

Do not use the update wizard.


NOTE:

The patch only patches the ECDSA public key
